sentences: Thomas Seltzer (born 27 July 1969), also known by his stage name Happy-Tom, is an American musician who is the bassist (originally drummer) and main songwriter for the band Turbonegro.
At six, in 1975, he moved to Nesodden in Akershus, Norway.
Seltzer is currently living in Oslo where he is working as a talkshow host and documentarist for the public Norwegian national television channel NRK.
